<quantity id="4CDEA6EF257E0C61FDD4FE46EDAB7C82" box="[609,708,438,465]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7907" metricValueMax="1.9304" metricValueMin="1.6509999999999998" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" unit="in" value="70.5" valueMax="76.0" valueMin="65.0">65–76 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C267089257E0C61FD7EFE47ECFF7C82" box="[715,912,439,465]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mediterraneus">
<emphasis id="B952D718257E0C61FD7EFE47ECFF7C82" box="[715,912,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">O. mediterraneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and no depigmented stripe along the anterior part of the lateral line (vs. usually present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C267089257E0C61FD24FE2BEC7E7CA7" baseAuthorityName="Steindachner" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[657,785,475,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Orthrias" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="angorae">
<emphasis id="B952D718257E0C61FD24FE2BEC7E7CA7" box="[657,785,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">O. angorae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It is further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C267089257E0C61FB3FFE2BEA207CA6" box="[1162,1359,475,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mediterraneus">
<emphasis id="B952D718257E0C61FB3FFE2BEA207CA6" box="[1162,1359,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">O. mediterraneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the tip of pectoral fin not reaching the pelvic-fin origin in male (vs. usually reaching).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C5881257E0C61FF72FDD2ED517F32" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B990B0A257E0C61FF72FDD2ED517F32" blockId="21.[151,1436,151,717]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis id="B952D718257E0C61FF72FDD2EE0E7F6F" bold="true" box="[199,353,546,572]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C267089257E0C61FEDEFDD3EDC87F6E" authorityName="Stoumboudi, Kottelat &amp; Barbieri" authorityYear="2006" box="[363,679,547,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="theophilii">
<emphasis id="B952D718257E0C61FEDEFDD3EDC87F6E" box="[363,679,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Oxynoemacheilus theophilii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in the Bakır River drainage in western 
<collectingCountry id="F3314B9A257E0C61FB57FDD3EA297F6E" box="[1250,1350,547,573]" name="Turkey" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
. It also occurs on the Greek island of Lesbos.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C5881257E0C61FF72FD9BECD37F9E" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B990B0A257E0C61FF72FD9BECD37F9E" blockId="21.[151,1436,151,717]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis id="B952D718257E0C61FF72FD9BEE547FD6" bold="true" box="[199,315,619,645]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Remarks.</emphasis>
Based on our COI dataset, 
<taxonomicName id="4C267089257E0C61FDCCFD9BEC687FD6" authorityName="Stoumboudi, Kottelat &amp; Barbieri" authorityYear="2006" box="[633,775,619,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="theophilii">
<emphasis id="B952D718257E0C61FDCCFD9BEC687FD6" box="[633,775,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">O. theophilii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well separated from all other studied 
<taxonomicName id="4C267089257E0C61FB60FD9BEF847FFA" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis id="B952D718257E0C61FB60FD9BEAF37FD6" box="[1237,1436,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Oxynoemacheilus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, including by a minimum K2P distance of 2.7% to 
<taxonomicName id="4C267089257E0C61FC88FD7FECF07FFA" box="[829,927,655,681]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eliasi">
<emphasis id="B952D718257E0C61FC88FD7FECF07FFA" box="[829,927,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">O. eliasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, its closest relative. It is also supported as a distinct species by the PTP approach, but not by the mPTP delimitation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
